    "caption": "Spring peeper, puddle jumper, creature of two very different worlds.",
    "shortDescription": "Frogs start life as fish-like tadpoles breathing through gills underwater, then grow legs, lose their tail, and hop onto land — all in a few weeks. Their smooth moist skin can absorb water and even oxygen directly, so they never really have to drink the usual way. Fun fact: The glass frog has nearly transparent skin on its belly — you can see its beating heart right through it."
